<item>
            <title>[SPARK-7236] AkkaUtils askWithReply sleeps indefinitely when a timeout exception is thrown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7236</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &lt;tt&gt;AkkaUtils.askWithReply&lt;/tt&gt; gets a TimeoutException, the default parameters &lt;tt&gt;maxAttempts = 1&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;retryInterval = Int.MaxValue&lt;/tt&gt; lead to the thread sleeping for a good while.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed this issue when testing for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6980&quot; title=&quot;Akka timeout exceptions indicate which conf controls them&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-6980&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-6980&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and using this function without invoking Spark jobs, so perhaps it acts differently in another context.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this function is on its final attempt to ask and it fails, it should return immediately.  Also, perhaps a better default &lt;tt&gt;retryInterval&lt;/tt&gt; would be &lt;tt&gt;0&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
